text:
<@U0260V1BX> The changes to the notifications CMS look great!! Thank you for doing that! Here are a few things I think we should add/change:  
1. Admins should be able to add a link with a title and url
2. Admins should be able to include a GIF
3. Only one media type per notification is displayed in app (i.e. video, gif, OR image). Perhaps we can add a drop down menu where the admin can choose between the allowable options?
4. It is possible to display an image in the notification and one media item in app, so we should still allow for admin to add an image in addition to a media item (This might be useful if they want to include a screenshot of the youtube video that will display in app or a still shot of a gif). However, we should make sure they know that the uploaded image will not be displayed in app in the event that a media item is added.

Tapping New Notification would open the screens outlined above with a back button
